The paper focuses on indoor scene understanding using deep neural networks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of physically-based rendering and 3D indoor scenes suggests a potential fit with graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The study of rendering methods and scene lighting for training with synthetic data also involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization of model performance (cs.LG).
